1
00:00:06,000 --> 00:00:07,600
Previously on Marshals.

2
00:00:07,980 --> 00:00:09,280
Casey, meet my marshals.

3
00:00:09,360 --> 00:00:10,980
Andrew, Miles, Bill.

4
00:00:11,340 --> 00:00:12,146
Welcome to the U.

5
00:00:12,226 --> 00:00:12,251
S.

6
00:00:12,331 --> 00:00:13,331
Marshals.

7
00:00:15,000 --> 00:00:16,720
You got eyes on a possible trigger, man?

8
00:00:16,800 --> 00:00:17,800
Black bag.

9
00:00:19,080 --> 00:00:20,640
David, get me that bomber.

10
00:00:24,240 --> 00:00:25,240
It's okay.

11
00:00:25,540 --> 00:00:26,540
You're okay now.

12
00:00:26,980 --> 00:00:29,260
Dutton's are born with
dysfunction in their blood.

13
00:00:29,340 --> 00:00:30,480
I'm changing paths.

14
00:00:31,060 --> 00:00:34,060
I'm trying to find a new
beginning for me and Tate.

15
00:00:51,930 --> 00:00:54,290
That bang town used to blow
off some steam on the range.

16
00:00:54,370 --> 00:00:57,090
Would you rather spend the
day chasing him or fishing?

17
00:00:57,170 --> 00:00:59,750
Catching more trout
than you is my priority.

18
00:00:59,830 --> 00:01:01,771
Beating you to the river is mine.

19
00:01:03,700 --> 00:01:04,700
Game on.

20
00:01:08,740 --> 00:01:12,564
It's gonna be hard to reel in all
them fish with just your hands.

21
00:01:43,620 --> 00:01:44,679
I got another one.

22
00:01:45,940 --> 00:01:47,705
Want me to pick a fly for you?

23
00:01:48,860 --> 00:01:51,095
I'm just scaring him down to you, son.

24
00:02:05,220 --> 00:02:06,455
Brings back memories.

25
00:02:09,790 --> 00:02:10,790
It's a good day.

26
00:02:14,000 --> 00:02:15,176
What about tomorrow?

27
00:02:16,180 --> 00:02:18,121
Ready to kick doors as a marshal?

28
00:02:18,540 --> 00:02:19,300
I'd be quiet.

29
00:02:19,380 --> 00:02:21,820
Just paperwork and the new guy nonsense.

30
00:02:21,900 --> 00:02:27,760
You sure you're ready for this change?

31
00:02:27,840 --> 00:02:31,330
A new start will do us both good.

32
00:02:31,410 --> 00:02:36,410
But who's gonna look over
East Camp with you working?

33
00:02:36,490 --> 00:02:41,230
Rip found some hands so I could
find a more permanent solution.

34
00:02:41,310 --> 00:02:46,730
That means tomorrow's
your new beginning too.

35
00:02:46,810 --> 00:02:49,490
Good.

36
00:02:49,570 --> 00:02:55,490
So after a day like this, I
know which time can stand still.

37
00:02:57,490 --> 00:03:04,490
So I'm looking over this HVT when Double
G, he walks back into the room dressed in
the clothes of the telly monster we just
swacked.

38
00:03:19,750 --> 00:03:21,670
Hat, pajamas, the whole get up.

39
00:03:21,750 --> 00:03:22,670
Yeah.

40
00:03:22,750 --> 00:03:23,750
18 for the round.

41
00:03:25,750 --> 00:03:27,670
How can you identify me this soon?

42
00:03:27,750 --> 00:03:28,750
He'll tell you.

43
00:03:36,620 --> 00:03:37,620
Oh.

44
00:03:38,620 --> 00:03:43,540
And since neither of us is asleep tonight,
only question is will be my place or
yours?

45
00:03:43,620 --> 00:03:45,540
Yeah, a girl loves to have options.

46
00:03:45,620 --> 00:03:46,540
Really?

47
00:03:46,620 --> 00:03:49,620
Like, should I spray you?

48
00:03:50,620 --> 00:03:52,620
Or stab you?

49
00:04:00,220 --> 00:04:01,140
A little hostile in here tonight.

50
00:04:01,220 --> 00:04:04,140
Especially the bartender.

51
00:04:04,220 --> 00:04:06,140
She's knives out for Cal.

52
00:04:06,220 --> 00:04:09,140
Her name's Maddie, and you're
talking out of your ass.

53
00:04:09,220 --> 00:04:10,140
Pardon.

54
00:04:10,220 --> 00:04:13,140
Ma'am, may I buy you a drink?

55
00:04:13,220 --> 00:04:15,140
Make up for my friend's two left feet.

56
00:04:15,220 --> 00:04:16,140
Ma'am?

57
00:04:16,220 --> 00:04:19,800
My abuela's a ma'am.

58
00:04:19,880 --> 00:04:20,800
No.

59
00:04:20,880 --> 00:04:21,800
Thank you.

60
00:04:21,880 --> 00:04:27,830
This 10 gallon hat wouldn't let him quit.

61
00:04:27,910 --> 00:04:30,830
I mean, it wouldn't kill you
to broaden your horizons.

62
00:04:30,910 --> 00:04:33,830
Come on, find some companionship.

63
00:04:33,910 --> 00:04:35,830
Is that why you have your
war buddy joining the team?

64
00:04:35,910 --> 00:04:39,830
No, look, I brought Casey in for the
same reason I brought both of you on.

65
00:04:39,910 --> 00:04:41,830
Okay, to sharpen the tip of the spear.

66
00:04:41,910 --> 00:04:43,830
The spear's pretty lethal already.

67
00:04:43,910 --> 00:04:47,830
When I go into battle, I need
teammates who have a fight.

68
00:04:47,910 --> 00:04:53,830
Whether it's a tenacious manhunter from
the Bronx, or a former res cop with fire
in his belly.

69
00:04:53,910 --> 00:04:59,340
We just want to make sure your shared past
isn't stepping on our toes in the present.

70
00:04:59,420 --> 00:05:04,740
New team, new dynamic.

71
00:05:04,820 --> 00:05:11,820
Bring to that.

72
00:05:15,000 --> 00:05:16,920
Bringing the smoke today.

73
00:05:17,000 --> 00:05:17,920
Leaving you behind, innit?

74
00:05:18,000 --> 00:05:18,920
Mm-hmm.

75
00:05:19,000 --> 00:05:26,000
Watch this.

76
00:05:27,420 --> 00:05:31,340
Bold move, embarrassing
the boss on the first day.

77
00:05:31,420 --> 00:05:32,340
Double or nothing?

78
00:05:32,420 --> 00:05:34,340
Hell no.

79
00:05:34,420 --> 00:05:39,340
It's the paying off loans from all the
money you took off of me in Afghanistan.

80
00:05:39,420 --> 00:05:41,340
Is this some sort of entry exam?

81
00:05:41,420 --> 00:05:46,340
Nope, just seeing how the lone wolf
is feeling joining the new pack.

82
00:05:46,420 --> 00:05:48,340
A fit man's never been my strong suit.

83
00:05:48,420 --> 00:05:55,100
Well, I know moving forward isn't easy,
but getting back into the fire's gonna do
you right.

84
00:05:55,180 --> 00:05:57,100
Well, then I'll get comfortable
being uncomfortable.

85
00:05:57,180 --> 00:05:58,100
You know what?

86
00:05:58,180 --> 00:06:02,220
I'll let your training day begin.

87
00:06:02,300 --> 00:06:09,300
Tori, gear cleaning.

88
00:06:44,740 --> 00:06:46,660
How else did you guys initiate me?

89
00:06:46,740 --> 00:06:48,660
Come on, we gotta break in the FNG.

90
00:06:48,740 --> 00:06:52,660
You know, why don't we just
welcome Casey as one of us?

91
00:06:52,740 --> 00:06:55,660
I mean, if hunting down those bombers
didn't initiate him, what will?

92
00:06:55,740 --> 00:06:58,660
Non-natives have no
appreciation for tradition.

93
00:06:58,740 --> 00:07:04,660
Hey, since we've all been shot at
together, let's just skip the formalities.

94
00:07:04,740 --> 00:07:08,910
Uh, I'm glad to join this outfit.

95
00:07:08,990 --> 00:07:09,910
See if you say that after the show.

96
00:07:09,990 --> 00:07:15,410
See if you say that after drinking
through a fire hose today.

97
00:07:15,490 --> 00:07:17,410
Yeah, I tread lightly, Miles.

98
00:07:17,490 --> 00:07:19,410
Casey's reasonable until he isn't.

99
00:07:19,490 --> 00:07:20,410
I'd ease him in.

100
00:07:20,490 --> 00:07:22,410
I gotta talk to Harry.

101
00:07:22,490 --> 00:07:24,410
Well, tour's pretty simple.

102
00:07:24,490 --> 00:07:25,410
Head's on now.

103
00:07:25,490 --> 00:07:26,410
Unisex.

104
00:07:26,490 --> 00:07:27,410
It's real intimate.

105
00:07:27,490 --> 00:07:34,490
Cal built this team to model after a SEAL
unit, but he failed to account for certain
differences, like teammates with two X
chromosomes.

106
00:07:35,490 --> 00:07:37,410
We're a toilet seat stays down unit.

107
00:07:37,490 --> 00:07:39,410
Bell runs 10 ship.

108
00:07:39,490 --> 00:07:41,410
Appreciate the intel.

109
00:07:41,490 --> 00:07:48,340
These are the cages.

110
00:07:48,420 --> 00:07:49,340
Huh.

111
00:07:49,420 --> 00:07:50,340
You waiting to move in?

112
00:07:50,420 --> 00:07:54,340
Uh, there's no use decorating
since I'm only passing through.

113
00:07:54,420 --> 00:08:01,420
These bags need reloading, so I'll
do that as you continue the tour.

114
00:08:07,650 --> 00:08:10,570
Here's your day.

115
00:08:10,650 --> 00:08:13,570
Feels like another meeting that could
have been an email, Marshal Gifford.

116
00:08:13,650 --> 00:08:17,570
Deputizing Dutton is one thing, but
making him a member of the team?

117
00:08:17,650 --> 00:08:22,570
Casey turns us into the elite unit that
you envisioned when you just stood this
team up.

118
00:08:22,650 --> 00:08:24,570
Yeah, but you got the
wrong pig by the tail.

119
00:08:24,650 --> 00:08:26,570
A Dutton wearing the Marshal star.

120
00:08:26,650 --> 00:08:28,570
It just doesn't sit right.

121
00:08:28,650 --> 00:08:35,650
He knows the area, he knows the people,
where the bodies are buried, and not to
mention, he's equipped to run any kind of
op this team face.

122
00:08:36,650 --> 00:08:43,650
But you don't find it odd that he's
jumping back into law enforcement when the
two biggest cold cases in this state are
his father's death and his brother's
disappearance?

123
00:08:45,650 --> 00:08:47,570
It's just a coincidence.

124
00:08:47,650 --> 00:08:50,570
There's no such thing as a
coincidence with the Duttons.

125
00:08:50,650 --> 00:08:52,570
Excuse me.

126
00:08:52,650 --> 00:08:56,420
Deputy Marshal Galvin, we have something.

127
00:08:56,500 --> 00:08:57,420
Please.

128
00:08:57,500 --> 00:09:01,420
Ops and investigations run out of here.

129
00:09:01,500 --> 00:09:03,420
I've been busy.

130
00:09:03,500 --> 00:09:05,420
Well, hunting dirtbags
is our bread and butter.

131
00:09:05,500 --> 00:09:07,420
We connect to the fusion center here.

132
00:09:07,500 --> 00:09:12,420
Maintaining two-way intelligence and
information flow is critical to our
mission.

133
00:09:12,500 --> 00:09:13,420
Right.

134
00:09:13,500 --> 00:09:14,420
Don't worry.

135
00:09:14,500 --> 00:09:16,420
You're here to be a gunslinger,
not a pencil pusher.

136
00:09:16,500 --> 00:09:21,420
These are our techs, analysts,
as well as our liaison team.

137
00:09:21,500 --> 00:09:25,420
Our liaisons that work with local,
state, and federal law enforcement.

138
00:09:25,500 --> 00:09:28,420
The lack of infrastructure
forces us to wear many hats.

139
00:09:28,500 --> 00:09:32,670
Especially now that we got
a trouble magnet on board.

140
00:09:32,750 --> 00:09:33,670
Fireplace is subtle.

141
00:09:33,750 --> 00:09:35,670
Compound used to be an old mill.

142
00:09:35,750 --> 00:09:41,670
Cal kept the blast furnace as a reminder
that this unit was forged in the fire.

143
00:09:41,750 --> 00:09:42,670
Okay, buddy, listen up.

144
00:09:42,750 --> 00:09:45,670
CI phoned in ahead on
a fugitive, Raul Garza.

145
00:09:45,750 --> 00:09:48,670
He's a member of the 406
Royals with federal warrants.

146
00:09:48,750 --> 00:09:49,670
Where's he at?

147
00:09:49,750 --> 00:09:51,670
Belgrade Trailer Park.

148
00:09:51,750 --> 00:09:53,670
People there got nothing to lose.

149
00:09:53,750 --> 00:09:55,670
Usually put up the biggest fight.

150
00:09:55,750 --> 00:09:57,670
Always takes us to the best places.

151
00:09:57,750 --> 00:09:58,670
Chock up.

152
00:09:58,750 --> 00:10:01,950
So much for easing you on.

153
00:10:02,030 --> 00:10:09,030
Informant says Garza's car
hasn't moved since last night.

154
00:10:13,800 --> 00:10:14,720
What's he doing here?

155
00:10:14,800 --> 00:10:15,720
This isn't Royals' turf.

156
00:10:15,800 --> 00:10:18,720
Royals blew up 18th Street
Mafia's stash house last month.

157
00:10:18,800 --> 00:10:20,720
Could be expanding the footprint.

158
00:10:20,800 --> 00:10:22,720
Maybe Garza's just
sampling the local product.

159
00:10:22,800 --> 00:10:24,720
Because Matheron's rampant out here.

160
00:10:24,800 --> 00:10:26,720
How many suspects on target?

161
00:10:26,800 --> 00:10:29,720
It's unknown, but hopefully they're
still sleeping or down hard on a bender.

162
00:10:29,800 --> 00:10:30,720
Think a door knock entry?

163
00:10:30,800 --> 00:10:31,720
No.

164
00:10:31,800 --> 00:10:33,720
We're gonna roll Garza
before his eyes even open.

165
00:10:33,800 --> 00:10:34,720
Okay?

166
00:10:34,800 --> 00:10:35,720
Fasten up.

167
00:10:35,800 --> 00:10:36,720
You want me in the stack?

168
00:10:36,800 --> 00:10:37,720
Train the wheels around.

169
00:10:37,800 --> 00:10:39,720
I'm gonna take square to patrol.

170
00:10:39,800 --> 00:10:41,720
Miles, Andrea, you're on me.

171
00:10:41,800 --> 00:10:43,720
Bell, you're outside the casing.

172
00:10:43,800 --> 00:10:45,720
I prefer team entry.

173
00:10:45,800 --> 00:10:47,720
Go slow after taking that round, okay?

174
00:10:47,800 --> 00:10:49,720
You don't know what baggage
you're carrying down the range.

175
00:10:49,800 --> 00:10:51,720
That's exactly why I gotta get
punched in the face and find out.

176
00:10:51,800 --> 00:10:52,720
Come on.

177
00:10:52,800 --> 00:10:53,720
You can swap.

178
00:10:53,800 --> 00:10:55,720
I'll watch Dutton.

179
00:10:55,800 --> 00:10:57,720
Yeah, okay.

180
00:10:57,800 --> 00:11:01,030
Let's move out.

181
00:11:01,110 --> 00:11:04,030
Little eager to jump out of the stack.

182
00:11:04,110 --> 00:11:06,030
First kill weighing on you?

183
00:11:06,110 --> 00:11:09,030
He's in the ground, not in my head.

184
00:11:09,110 --> 00:11:10,030
Uh-huh.

185
00:11:10,110 --> 00:11:12,213
U.

186
00:11:12,293 --> 00:11:14,397
S.

187
00:11:14,477 --> 00:11:21,477
Marshal!

188
00:11:23,210 --> 00:11:30,210
I thought we missed one hell of a party.

189
00:12:01,380 --> 00:12:03,300
Suspect's out breathing death.

190
00:12:03,380 --> 00:12:04,300
He was coming.

191
00:12:04,380 --> 00:12:09,790
He was in for a world of
hurt if he made it to me.

192
00:12:09,870 --> 00:12:15,560
High job.

193
00:12:15,640 --> 00:12:19,220
We're in Montana.

194
00:12:19,300 --> 00:12:21,220
Not a war zone.

195
00:12:21,300 --> 00:12:25,770
Cold habits.

196
00:12:25,850 --> 00:12:31,390
I thought Garza was gonna
alligator roll you, Cal.

197
00:12:31,470 --> 00:12:33,390
I handled my business
just like the rest of you.

198
00:12:33,470 --> 00:12:35,390
It was flawless up.

199
00:12:35,470 --> 00:12:36,390
Nearly flawless.

200
00:12:36,470 --> 00:12:38,390
Popped a damn button
taking that perp down.

201
00:12:38,470 --> 00:12:43,390
Oh, I'll be sure to note your shirt
as a casualty in the after action.

202
00:12:43,470 --> 00:12:45,390
It's just like old times, huh?

203
00:12:45,470 --> 00:12:47,390
Kicking doors and rolling up dirt bags.

204
00:12:47,470 --> 00:12:50,390
Except back then I was on your
six, not on the sidelines.

205
00:12:50,470 --> 00:12:55,140
Excuse me.

206
00:12:55,220 --> 00:12:57,140
Tats on the guy we collared with Garza.

207
00:12:57,220 --> 00:13:00,140
Mark him as a member of the
Aryan Brethren of Idaho.

208
00:13:00,220 --> 00:13:02,140
And the pills he was
holding were fentanyl.

209
00:13:02,220 --> 00:13:04,140
White nationalist and Latin gang leader.

210
00:13:04,220 --> 00:13:05,140
Make an odd couple.

211
00:13:05,220 --> 00:13:07,140
Drugs are a hell of a uniform.

212
00:13:07,220 --> 00:13:08,140
Oh.

213
00:13:08,220 --> 00:13:10,140
Hey, I got a situation on the ranch.

214
00:13:10,220 --> 00:13:12,140
You mind if I go deal with it?

215
00:13:12,220 --> 00:13:15,140
Oh, you didn't get to kick doors, so
you're taking your ball and going home.

216
00:13:15,220 --> 00:13:20,140
Hey, let the DA know about the fentanyl
and send Garza and the Aryan upstate to
Helena, okay?

217
00:13:20,220 --> 00:13:22,140
I'm rolling with Casey.

218
00:13:22,220 --> 00:13:23,140
All right, sorry.

219
00:13:23,220 --> 00:13:24,140
I can take care of it on my own.

220
00:13:24,220 --> 00:13:27,140
Team needs to learn that one is none.

221
00:13:27,220 --> 00:13:29,140
All right.

222
00:13:29,220 --> 00:13:31,140
See y'all.

223
00:13:31,220 --> 00:13:33,140
What business do the Aryans
have with the royal family?

224
00:13:33,220 --> 00:13:34,140
I don't know.

225
00:13:34,220 --> 00:13:37,140
The Aryans were on my radar at ATF.

226
00:13:37,220 --> 00:13:41,140
A group of them were behind the plot
to kidnap the governor of Idaho.

227
00:13:41,220 --> 00:13:43,140
The cattle told us to ship them out.

228
00:13:43,220 --> 00:13:48,870
We're here to wage a war on violence,
not just roll up foot soldiers.

229
00:13:48,950 --> 00:13:50,870
A little digging can't hurt.

230
00:13:50,950 --> 00:13:54,890
The stallion broke clean through.

231
00:13:54,970 --> 00:14:01,970
From man hunting to horse hunting.

232
00:14:10,980 --> 00:14:13,900
Is that the kind of call out
you do, like, as a cow cop?

233
00:14:13,980 --> 00:14:14,900
You may joke.

234
00:14:14,980 --> 00:14:17,900
That horse on the loose is
a grenade with a pin pulled.

235
00:14:17,980 --> 00:14:19,900
That's not a horse.

236
00:14:19,980 --> 00:14:21,900
That's anger with legs.

237
00:14:21,980 --> 00:14:22,900
Yeah.

238
00:14:22,980 --> 00:14:24,900
Something tells me he's
not going to go easy.

239
00:14:24,980 --> 00:14:31,180
I don't know your plan, but I don't
think I can be your QRF on this, pal.

240
00:14:31,260 --> 00:14:32,180
Plan?

241
00:14:32,260 --> 00:14:36,620
I'm making this up as I go.

242
00:14:36,700 --> 00:14:43,700
Casey Dutton, U.

243
00:14:48,743 --> 00:14:50,168
S.

244
00:14:50,248 --> 00:14:57,248
Marshal Harry Gifford, makes me your boss.

245
00:15:21,860 --> 00:15:23,780
It feels like I'm working
for everybody today.

246
00:15:23,860 --> 00:15:25,780
Oh, you two are out gallivanting.

247
00:15:25,860 --> 00:15:27,780
Andrea made a hell of a discovery.

248
00:15:27,860 --> 00:15:29,780
This is the first time I've
ever been on a mission.

249
00:15:29,860 --> 00:15:31,780
I've never been on a mission before.

250
00:15:31,860 --> 00:15:36,780
There's a fentanyl deal going down today
between the Aryans and the 406 Royals.

251
00:15:36,860 --> 00:15:38,780
How'd you put that together?

252
00:15:38,860 --> 00:15:43,780
The Aryan, Lenny Nelson, two-time loser,
he came to Bozeman to let the Royals test
the fentanyl.

253
00:15:43,860 --> 00:15:46,780
Well, they're going to call off that
deal as soon as they realize they're MIA.

254
00:15:46,860 --> 00:15:49,780
Well, Nelson says he and Garza were
just meeting to test the product.

255
00:15:49,860 --> 00:15:55,780
And after they signed off, they let
themselves enjoy a long weekend consuming
product.

256
00:15:55,860 --> 00:15:57,780
And Garza, he backed all that up?

257
00:15:57,860 --> 00:15:59,780
Well, he wasn't as charmed
by Deputy Cruz as Nelson.

258
00:15:59,860 --> 00:16:00,780
You know, the DEA can't spin up and down.

259
00:16:00,860 --> 00:16:02,780
The DEA can't spin up in time to get here.

260
00:16:02,860 --> 00:16:04,780
So we're on agent assist.

261
00:16:04,860 --> 00:16:07,780
FBI chatter says the Aryans
are plotting something big.

262
00:16:07,860 --> 00:16:10,780
Yeah, selling the fentanyl is probably
going to be how they finance it.

263
00:16:10,860 --> 00:16:13,780
Well, this unit was designed
for big game hunting.

264
00:16:13,860 --> 00:16:16,780
I mean, Aryan Brethren would
be quite the trophy on my wall.

265
00:16:16,860 --> 00:16:18,780
Do you have the muscle for that?

266
00:16:18,860 --> 00:16:21,780
Well, Cal sold you his last
piece to his dream team.

267
00:16:21,860 --> 00:16:24,780
Prime chance for you to
back those big words up.

268
00:16:24,860 --> 00:16:26,780
Okay, so where's the deal going down?

269
00:16:26,860 --> 00:16:29,780
Just over the Wyoming border, a
place called the Zone of Death.

270
00:16:29,860 --> 00:16:30,780
I don't know.

271
00:16:30,860 --> 00:16:34,780
Apparently, it got its name because
there's no citizens, no law enforcement,
no judges or juries.

272
00:16:34,860 --> 00:16:36,780
So there's no way to prosecute crimes.

273
00:16:36,860 --> 00:16:41,780
The local legend has been a dumping ground
for the region's most depraved criminals.

274
00:16:41,860 --> 00:16:43,780
There is no way that's true.

275
00:16:43,860 --> 00:16:44,780
Well, it doesn't.

276
00:16:44,860 --> 00:16:47,780
They've been here for over a century.

277
00:16:47,860 --> 00:16:50,780
Does this tale get passed
down through generations?

278
00:16:50,860 --> 00:16:57,860
No, it's the first time I'm hearing of it.

279
00:17:05,700 --> 00:17:07,620
Surveillance cameras in gear.

280
00:17:07,700 --> 00:17:09,620
Rangefinder, too.

281
00:17:09,700 --> 00:17:11,620
I need all the eyes I
can get watching my back.

282
00:17:11,700 --> 00:17:13,620
He's got this deal in his feels.

283
00:17:13,700 --> 00:17:15,620
You undermining me with Harry?

284
00:17:15,700 --> 00:17:18,620
I was finding a fight to
pick like you hired me to do.

285
00:17:18,700 --> 00:17:20,620
I'm still sore from our last ride.

286
00:17:20,700 --> 00:17:21,620
Are the horses my punishment?

287
00:17:21,700 --> 00:17:22,620
No.

288
00:17:22,700 --> 00:17:25,620
Just the best way to keep a low
profile in the Zone of Death.

289
00:17:25,700 --> 00:17:30,620
Well, taking down a deal between two
dangerous gangs doesn't exactly scream low
profile.

290
00:17:30,700 --> 00:17:32,620
That's why we're only busting the air.

291
00:17:32,700 --> 00:17:33,620
And let the royals walk?

292
00:17:33,700 --> 00:17:35,620
They distribute meth to the rez.

293
00:17:35,700 --> 00:17:38,620
Push that fentanyl onto Broken
Rock, it'll spread like wildfire.

294
00:17:38,700 --> 00:17:39,620
Don't worry.

295
00:17:39,700 --> 00:17:40,620
Okay?

296
00:17:40,700 --> 00:17:42,620
See him for the DEA to sweep up.

297
00:17:42,700 --> 00:17:44,545
The Aryans are planning an attack.

298
00:17:44,625 --> 00:17:45,620
They take priority.

299
00:17:45,700 --> 00:17:49,780
Excuse me.

300
00:17:49,860 --> 00:17:53,671
You gotta hand it to her.

301
00:17:53,751 --> 00:17:59,740
I never saw my dad when he was on duty.

302
00:17:59,820 --> 00:18:02,740
Yep, found the balance
that eludes most of us.

303
00:18:02,820 --> 00:18:04,740
She's a remarkable woman.

304
00:18:04,820 --> 00:18:07,620
As a mother.

305
00:18:07,700 --> 00:18:14,700
Mm-hmm.

306
00:18:20,040 --> 00:18:21,960
I was hoping to have a word.

307
00:18:22,040 --> 00:18:22,960
Sir?

308
00:18:23,040 --> 00:18:26,960
You Duttons always had a
soft spot for public service.

309
00:18:27,040 --> 00:18:30,960
Livestock Commission,
Attorney General, Governor.

310
00:18:31,040 --> 00:18:32,960
Just doing our part.

311
00:18:33,040 --> 00:18:33,960
Yeah, but for whom?

312
00:18:34,040 --> 00:18:40,960
Seems to me it was always in service of
your family, or Yellowstone Ranch, or some
form of vengeance.

313
00:18:41,040 --> 00:18:42,514
Well, the Yellowstone's gone.

314
00:18:42,594 --> 00:18:43,960
Same for most of my family.

315
00:18:44,040 --> 00:18:47,960
And as for vengeance,
the day's still young.

316
00:18:48,040 --> 00:18:51,960
You got a sharp tongue,
just like your father.

317
00:18:52,040 --> 00:18:53,960
We had a history, you know.

318
00:18:54,040 --> 00:18:56,960
Yeah, he used to talk about that a lot.

319
00:18:57,040 --> 00:19:04,040
Really?

320
00:19:13,820 --> 00:19:18,540
It's nice of your husband
and kid to drop by.

321
00:19:18,620 --> 00:19:21,540
It was inappropriate during work hours.

322
00:19:21,620 --> 00:19:25,550
It won't happen again.

323
00:19:25,630 --> 00:19:28,310
Are you kidding?

324
00:19:28,390 --> 00:19:31,067
Our family could have swung
by when I was deployed.

325
00:19:31,147 --> 00:19:32,310
I might still have one.

326
00:19:32,390 --> 00:19:36,310
This job keeps me around a lot more
than working undercover with ATF did.

327
00:19:36,390 --> 00:19:40,620
They're just adjusting to the new norm.

328
00:19:40,700 --> 00:19:45,380
I admire you prioritizing your family.

329
00:19:45,460 --> 00:19:50,980
It takes a lot more discipline than I had.

330
00:19:51,060 --> 00:19:53,980
You don't think your husband would stop by
because he's worried you took that round,
though?

331
00:19:54,060 --> 00:19:56,980
If I let him clean teeth,
he lets me fight crime.

332
00:19:57,060 --> 00:20:00,520
You didn't tell him, did you?

333
00:20:00,600 --> 00:20:05,860
You know, building walls shuts out
the people that you care about.

334
00:20:05,940 --> 00:20:06,860
They're not walls.

335
00:20:06,940 --> 00:20:13,940
Zone of death, my ass.

336
00:20:23,220 --> 00:20:25,140
There's nothing out here.

337
00:20:25,220 --> 00:20:32,220
Awful quiet, cowboy.

338
00:20:36,750 --> 00:20:39,670
What's been banging like a powwow
drum since we left Bozeman?

339
00:20:39,750 --> 00:20:41,670
You worried?

340
00:20:41,750 --> 00:20:44,670
Tip of the spear goes where it's pointed.

341
00:20:44,750 --> 00:20:47,670
Even if it's the last
place you want to be.

342
00:20:47,750 --> 00:20:49,670
So you do know this place?

343
00:20:49,750 --> 00:20:52,670
Op just has a lot of unknowns.

344
00:20:52,750 --> 00:20:54,670
Probably got enough of those in your life.

345
00:20:54,750 --> 00:21:01,750
Do you really not know
where your brother Jamie is?

346
00:21:04,120 --> 00:21:07,040
At least when my dad got
killed, we knew he was gone.

347
00:21:07,120 --> 00:21:09,040
Gave us closure.

348
00:21:09,120 --> 00:21:15,020
Family history like yours?

349
00:21:15,100 --> 00:21:22,100
I'm sure it's hard to turn the page.

350
00:21:29,740 --> 00:21:30,660
for a takedown.

351
00:21:30,740 --> 00:21:32,660
Spotty comms, y'all.

352
00:21:32,740 --> 00:21:37,660
Rough terrain, wild animals, and two
violent gangs, so everybody's gotta be
dialed in.

353
00:21:37,740 --> 00:21:39,660
Trackers are prepped
with royals as vehicles.

354
00:21:39,740 --> 00:21:42,660
Better work so the DEA can help them down.

355
00:21:42,740 --> 00:21:44,660
All right, Bell, handle
the trackers and miles.

356
00:21:44,740 --> 00:21:47,660
Andrew and I, we're gonna run surveillance
from that rock outcrop over there.

357
00:21:47,740 --> 00:21:49,660
In case you just watched Bell on mile six.

358
00:21:49,740 --> 00:21:51,660
This'll work for Overwatch.

359
00:21:51,740 --> 00:21:54,660
Interdicting the Aryans
on horses is a tall order.

360
00:21:54,740 --> 00:21:58,660
That's exactly why we're gonna hit them
after the deal when the guard's down,
okay?

361
00:21:58,740 --> 00:22:03,760
Casey, you got me?

362
00:22:03,840 --> 00:22:06,760
Line the dog, drive the plane.

363
00:22:06,840 --> 00:22:08,760
Uh...

364
00:22:08,840 --> 00:22:11,760
Something reflecting across that ravine.

365
00:22:11,840 --> 00:22:15,170
That junk over there.

366
00:22:15,250 --> 00:22:17,170
Aerial ground's more than just a rumor.

367
00:22:17,250 --> 00:22:20,540
It's almost drop time.

368
00:22:20,620 --> 00:22:22,540
Ghosts in the ravine,
they do not concern us.

369
00:22:22,620 --> 00:22:24,540
Move into position, let's go.

370
00:22:24,620 --> 00:22:26,540
Come on, move into
position, let's go, y'all.

371
00:22:26,620 --> 00:22:33,620
Three trucks inbound.

372
00:22:47,060 --> 00:22:48,980
Sensitive windows.

373
00:22:49,060 --> 00:22:50,980
Okay, Bell, target's incoming.

374
00:22:51,060 --> 00:22:51,980
Good copy.

375
00:22:52,060 --> 00:22:59,060
Got eyes on two SUVs coming from the east.

376
00:23:17,130 --> 00:23:21,960
Aryans.

377
00:23:22,040 --> 00:23:23,960
Bell, royals are in the pickups.

378
00:23:24,040 --> 00:23:25,960
Roger that.

379
00:23:26,040 --> 00:23:32,950
Moving into position.

380
00:23:33,030 --> 00:23:33,950
We're hitting.

381
00:23:34,030 --> 00:23:38,770
Got 11 suspects on the ground.

382
00:23:38,850 --> 00:23:42,500
Casey, something's about to pop off.

383
00:23:42,580 --> 00:23:48,380
Everybody's carrying him, but
nobody seems ready to go hot.

384
00:23:48,460 --> 00:23:51,850
Fentanyl's been handed over.

385
00:23:51,930 --> 00:23:53,850
Yeah, where's the cash?

386
00:23:53,930 --> 00:23:55,850
Money exchange should
not be this complicated.

387
00:23:55,930 --> 00:23:58,850
Bell, you're clear to move in position.

388
00:23:58,930 --> 00:24:00,850
We gotta get that truck alive, Bell.

389
00:24:00,930 --> 00:24:01,850
Good copy.

390
00:24:01,930 --> 00:24:08,580
All clear, Bell.

391
00:24:08,660 --> 00:24:13,650
What the hell are they looking at?

392
00:24:13,730 --> 00:24:17,020
Can't ID.

393
00:24:17,100 --> 00:24:21,767
Bell, you got company.

394
00:24:21,847 --> 00:24:24,140
Take cover.

395
00:24:24,220 --> 00:24:27,740
Bell, beat feet.

396
00:24:27,820 --> 00:24:30,486
Bandits camped out on Bell's paws.

397
00:24:30,566 --> 00:24:33,070
The vehicle's blocking my angle.

398
00:24:33,150 --> 00:24:35,070
Miles, move up to cover Bell.

399
00:24:35,150 --> 00:24:39,910
Moving.

400
00:24:39,990 --> 00:24:41,354
Got an issue.

401
00:24:41,434 --> 00:24:41,910
Over.

402
00:24:41,990 --> 00:24:42,910
Miles, are you in position?

403
00:24:42,990 --> 00:24:47,930
I say again, Miles, are you in position?

404
00:24:48,010 --> 00:24:51,074
Bell's just hanging out in the wind.

405
00:24:51,154 --> 00:24:53,170
We gotta get down there.

406
00:24:53,250 --> 00:24:54,800
Okay, Miles, we're up.

407
00:24:54,880 --> 00:24:55,170
Over.

408
00:24:55,250 --> 00:24:59,250
Cal, that royal's right on top of Miles.

409
00:24:59,330 --> 00:25:02,250
The whole point was to avoid
getting into a gunfight.

410
00:25:02,330 --> 00:25:03,207
Andrew's right.

411
00:25:03,287 --> 00:25:05,250
We gotta hold on to what we got.

412
00:25:05,330 --> 00:25:07,250
If we don't move, it's Roaner all over.

413
00:25:07,330 --> 00:25:14,130
Okay, don't engage unless you have to.

414
00:25:16,760 --> 00:25:17,680
What the hell was that?

415
00:25:17,760 --> 00:25:24,760
That's a bomb.

416
00:25:29,220 --> 00:25:32,014
Aryans aren't planning an attack.

417
00:25:32,094 --> 00:25:34,540
They're about to execute one.

418
00:25:34,620 --> 00:25:41,620
Bomb could kill everyone on the ground.

419
00:26:07,890 --> 00:26:12,050
And now it's in the wind.

420
00:26:12,130 --> 00:26:19,130
I can't even get a signal.

421
00:26:34,540 --> 00:26:36,460
Decision to bring horses isn't helping.

422
00:26:36,540 --> 00:26:38,361
Casey, the lead Aryan
SUV is carrying a bomb.

423
00:26:38,441 --> 00:26:39,460
I need you to enter it in.

424
00:26:39,540 --> 00:26:44,860
I need you to lock in, okay?

425
00:26:44,940 --> 00:26:48,860
Breathe, aim low, and squeeze,
otherwise Bell's dead.

426
00:26:48,940 --> 00:26:49,860
All right?

427
00:26:49,940 --> 00:26:50,860
Yeah.

428
00:26:50,940 --> 00:26:51,860
Cover me.

429
00:26:51,940 --> 00:26:58,940
Okay.

430
00:27:00,140 --> 00:27:05,430
Okay, cover Bell.

431
00:27:05,510 --> 00:27:12,510
I'm moving down, all right?

432
00:27:14,040 --> 00:27:15,960
Bell, I'm almost through your balls.

433
00:27:16,040 --> 00:27:16,960
Okay.

434
00:27:17,040 --> 00:27:18,051
Okay, blank him.

435
00:27:18,131 --> 00:27:19,960
Get Bell back into the spot.

436
00:27:20,040 --> 00:27:21,960
Could use Casey's gun right now.

437
00:27:22,040 --> 00:27:23,560
You shoot, I move.

438
00:27:23,640 --> 00:27:25,160
I shoot, you move.

439
00:27:25,240 --> 00:27:25,960
Let's go.

440
00:27:26,040 --> 00:27:33,040
Two rows are moving on you.

441
00:28:22,280 --> 00:28:22,976
That's a good idea.

442
00:28:23,056 --> 00:28:24,200
Okay, I'm gonna move to cover.

443
00:28:24,280 --> 00:28:25,836
You both block the car, so let's go.

444
00:28:25,916 --> 00:28:26,200
Come on.

445
00:28:26,280 --> 00:28:33,280
No, let's cover them.

446
00:28:36,244 --> 00:28:43,244
I'm taking right.

447
00:28:44,310 --> 00:28:50,230
On the ground!

448
00:28:50,310 --> 00:28:52,199
You guys watch those.

449
00:28:52,279 --> 00:28:53,230
Don't move.

450
00:28:53,310 --> 00:28:54,365
On the ground!

451
00:28:54,445 --> 00:28:56,230
Hands behind your back!

452
00:28:56,310 --> 00:29:01,660
Cover.

453
00:29:01,740 --> 00:29:02,740
Hey, guys.

454
00:29:03,740 --> 00:29:04,740
Where's Casey?

455
00:29:17,200 --> 00:29:24,200
It's gonna be slow, and
it's gonna be painful.

456
00:31:14,760 --> 00:31:15,680
Please.

457
00:31:15,760 --> 00:31:22,760
No, didn't make it to Bozeman, and the
bomb didn't make it to the federal
courthouse in Idaho.

458
00:32:35,580 --> 00:32:38,500
Well, Idaho State Police
picked the remaining Aryans up.

459
00:32:38,580 --> 00:32:43,500
One said they were planning on
moving the bomb straight to Target.

460
00:32:43,580 --> 00:32:46,500
You earned your marshal
money today, Casey.

461
00:32:46,580 --> 00:32:48,580
Guess the training wheels are off.

462
00:32:49,580 --> 00:32:50,500
I think, though.

463
00:32:50,580 --> 00:32:52,500
There were five Aryans on Target.

464
00:32:52,580 --> 00:32:56,500
Three were arrested,
one killed in the SUV.

465
00:32:56,580 --> 00:33:03,580
He's on a death, I guess.

466
00:33:04,750 --> 00:33:09,740
Time to baptize Casey.

467
00:33:09,820 --> 00:33:11,740
Tradition.

468
00:33:11,820 --> 00:33:13,740
Non-alcoholic in your case.

469
00:33:13,820 --> 00:33:16,740
Good thing, considering
what he's capable of sober.

470
00:33:16,820 --> 00:33:17,740
Hey.

471
00:33:17,820 --> 00:33:19,740
To Casey.

472
00:33:19,820 --> 00:33:21,740
New guy, no more.

473
00:33:21,820 --> 00:33:24,220
Cheers.

474
00:33:24,300 --> 00:33:25,220
Go, go, go.

475
00:33:25,300 --> 00:33:26,220
Go, go, go.

476
00:33:26,300 --> 00:33:27,220
Go, go, go.

477
00:33:27,300 --> 00:33:28,220
Go, go, go.

478
00:33:28,300 --> 00:33:29,220
Go, go, go.

479
00:33:29,300 --> 00:33:30,220
Go, go, go.

480
00:33:30,300 --> 00:33:37,300
My conquering heroes, FBI, ATF, and
Homeland Security are licking my boots
over this win.

481
00:33:46,020 --> 00:33:47,940
Thwarting a domestic terrorist attack?

482
00:33:48,020 --> 00:33:50,940
Can your wall fit a big
game trophy that size?

483
00:33:51,020 --> 00:33:53,940
Shouldn't ease any doubts
you have about Casey.

484
00:33:54,020 --> 00:33:55,940
Because he won us the victory today.

485
00:33:56,020 --> 00:34:00,770
Giving credit to the guy who
overruled you on the battlefield.

486
00:34:00,850 --> 00:34:03,400
Dunn was insubordinate.

487
00:34:03,480 --> 00:34:05,400
There's a surprise.

488
00:34:05,480 --> 00:34:07,400
Best idea wins on my team.

489
00:34:07,480 --> 00:34:10,400
Did Casey run roughshod over Cal?

490
00:34:10,480 --> 00:34:11,400
No.

491
00:34:11,480 --> 00:34:13,400
He was quiet before things got kinetic.

492
00:34:13,480 --> 00:34:15,400
Like he had something on his mind?

493
00:34:15,480 --> 00:34:17,400
His own agenda, perhaps?

494
00:34:17,480 --> 00:34:18,400
I don't know.

495
00:34:18,480 --> 00:34:20,400
But when I brought up his
brother, he got spooked.

496
00:34:20,480 --> 00:34:22,400
Casey doesn't spook.

497
00:34:22,480 --> 00:34:24,400
Maybe he does when he's hiding something.

498
00:34:24,480 --> 00:34:25,400
Like what?

499
00:34:25,480 --> 00:34:28,400
For keeping us off the scent
of his fugitive brother.

500
00:34:28,480 --> 00:34:33,400
If he joined this unit for some nefarious
reasons, I'm not going to let him get away
with it.

501
00:34:33,480 --> 00:34:35,400
Now, who's doing the after action?

502
00:34:35,480 --> 00:34:36,400
I'll do it.

503
00:34:36,480 --> 00:34:43,480
You all right?

504
00:34:48,080 --> 00:34:50,000
Guy killed still in my head.

505
00:34:50,080 --> 00:34:52,000
I know I'm the real new guy here.

506
00:34:52,080 --> 00:34:56,500
I wish I could be the new guy again.

507
00:34:56,580 --> 00:35:01,280
I didn't freeze up out there.

508
00:35:01,360 --> 00:35:04,280
My people think killing a
Rattler is a transgression.

509
00:35:04,360 --> 00:35:06,280
Bad omen, even.

510
00:35:06,360 --> 00:35:12,010
There's always going to be a snake.

511
00:35:12,090 --> 00:35:15,010
You can't reason with it
or hope it'll back down.

512
00:35:15,090 --> 00:35:19,480
Gotta be more dangerous than it
is or this job may not be for you.

513
00:35:19,560 --> 00:35:20,480
That's okay.

514
00:35:20,560 --> 00:35:27,560
I thought our six-play battle was going
to be the most intense action today.

515
00:35:35,150 --> 00:35:37,070
What was that about us
not being in a war zone?

516
00:35:37,150 --> 00:35:38,070
Back in the teams.

517
00:35:38,150 --> 00:35:42,070
I could always count on you
being dialed in downrange.

518
00:35:42,150 --> 00:35:46,070
You seemed a little bit out
of it when we got on target.

519
00:35:46,150 --> 00:35:49,600
Yeah.

520
00:35:49,680 --> 00:35:54,710
Grappling with some skeletons I'm
trying to keep in my family's closet.

521
00:35:54,790 --> 00:35:56,710
Operate when you got
ghosts hanging over you.

522
00:35:56,790 --> 00:35:58,710
And there was definitely one on the op.

523
00:35:58,790 --> 00:36:02,760
Ruiner.

524
00:36:02,840 --> 00:36:05,760
Bring them up like that, it's just...

525
00:36:05,840 --> 00:36:06,760
A cheap shot.

526
00:36:06,840 --> 00:36:10,760
It wasn't a cheap shot,
it was a targeted one.

527
00:36:10,840 --> 00:36:12,760
It kept history from it beating itself.

528
00:36:12,840 --> 00:36:19,840
I guess Stutton's known as
the Monopoly and Scout, right?

529
00:36:44,800 --> 00:36:46,720
One second, you're backing me.

530
00:36:46,800 --> 00:36:48,720
The next case, he's calling the shots.

531
00:36:48,800 --> 00:36:50,720
Wouldn't be sitting there if
Casey hadn't taken action.

532
00:36:50,800 --> 00:36:52,720
No, that is not my issue.

533
00:36:52,800 --> 00:36:55,720
Your war buddy manipulating
you in the heat of battle is.

534
00:36:55,800 --> 00:36:58,970
What does Ruiner mean, anyway?

535
00:36:59,050 --> 00:37:04,050
Why don't we focus on your
shotting intel instead?

536
00:37:04,130 --> 00:37:08,050
Well, it would look a whole lot different
right now if I hadn't uncovered that deal.

537
00:37:08,130 --> 00:37:12,050
Those attaboys you got from
Gifford and gave to Casey?

538
00:37:12,130 --> 00:37:13,050
They should have been for me.

539
00:37:13,130 --> 00:37:14,050
Oh, I see.

540
00:37:14,130 --> 00:37:17,050
Gifford, you take it
back to your old team,

541
00:37:17,130 --> 00:37:20,050
and you're just upset because you
didn't get the credit you deserve.

542
00:37:20,130 --> 00:37:22,050
Is that how it works?

543
00:37:22,130 --> 00:37:26,050
This is compliments of the cowboy.

544
00:37:26,130 --> 00:37:33,130
He says, sorry, ma'am.

545
00:37:42,850 --> 00:37:44,770
Want to hear some more SEAL stories?

546
00:37:44,850 --> 00:37:51,850
I'm going.

547
00:37:59,050 --> 00:38:06,050
You're a brave man coming back for more.

548
00:38:07,910 --> 00:38:10,830
A cowboy worth his salt gets
right back on the horse.

549
00:38:10,910 --> 00:38:13,830
Especially when chasing
something as health-bred as you.

550
00:38:13,910 --> 00:38:16,830
I can't promise I won't buck a gun.

551
00:38:16,910 --> 00:38:23,910
I'm counting on it.

552
00:38:29,100 --> 00:38:35,020
Who knew playing Cupid would
have you like pig and slop?

553
00:38:35,100 --> 00:38:39,020
This chair's empty if
you've got a minute to chat.

554
00:38:39,100 --> 00:38:44,520
I'd like to share more than
just war stories with you.

555
00:38:44,600 --> 00:38:46,520
You want more than a minute.

556
00:38:46,600 --> 00:38:53,600
But I don't have that to give.

557
00:38:54,580 --> 00:38:58,500
Hey, thought you'd be
prioritizing your family.

558
00:38:58,580 --> 00:39:02,500
And expose them to what I'm
carrying away from today?

559
00:39:02,580 --> 00:39:05,500
You know, when I was operating,

560
00:39:05,580 --> 00:39:08,500
the battlefield was
thousands of miles from home.

561
00:39:08,580 --> 00:39:15,260
Gave me a chance to shed
some of the toxins from war.

562
00:39:15,340 --> 00:39:20,800
Yeah, Buffer Zone sounds
real nice right about now.

563
00:39:20,880 --> 00:39:22,800
Nice job.

564
00:39:22,880 --> 00:39:25,800
You've got to find a way
to let go of a fighter

565
00:39:25,880 --> 00:39:27,800
that people care about and let go of us.

566
00:39:27,880 --> 00:39:30,800
So you're saying drinking with
you is in the best interest

567
00:39:30,880 --> 00:39:33,800
of my family?

568
00:39:33,880 --> 00:39:35,800
Better get you to step.

569
00:39:35,880 --> 00:39:42,880
Where you been?

570
00:40:06,460 --> 00:40:08,380
Reinforcing the corrals.

571
00:40:08,460 --> 00:40:10,380
More things change.

572
00:40:10,460 --> 00:40:14,710
How'd it go today?

573
00:40:14,790 --> 00:40:16,710
Yeah, Yellowstone might be gone,

574
00:40:16,790 --> 00:40:21,020
but there's still some
landmines left behind.

575
00:40:21,100 --> 00:40:23,020
How about you?

576
00:40:23,100 --> 00:40:26,260
I don't know.

577
00:40:26,340 --> 00:40:30,020
I didn't find my new beginning.

578
00:40:30,100 --> 00:40:32,020
They'll find you.

579
00:40:32,100 --> 00:40:33,020
When?

580
00:40:33,100 --> 00:40:37,840
When you're ready.

581
00:40:37,920 --> 00:40:39,840
I went and saw Grandpa Long today.

582
00:40:39,920 --> 00:40:42,840
He wants us to honor Mom at
the Remembrance Ceremony.

583
00:40:42,920 --> 00:40:46,880
Next month.

584
00:40:46,960 --> 00:40:47,880
Sure.

585
00:40:47,960 --> 00:40:50,880
Asked about borrowing
your favorite necklace.

586
00:40:50,960 --> 00:40:55,090
Any idea where it is?

587
00:40:55,170 --> 00:40:56,090
I'll look tomorrow.

588
00:40:56,170 --> 00:41:00,740
Spent too much time worried
about buried treasure today.
